text: Jan Štefan (born 2 September 1943) is a Czech rower who represented Czechoslovakia. He competed at the 1964 Summer Olympics in Tokyo with the men's coxed four where they were eliminated in the round one repêchage. ==References== Category:1943 births Category:Living people Category:Czechoslovak male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of Czechoslovakia Category:Rowers at the 1964 Summer Olympics Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
